        <property name="text" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.StringAttribute" value="Creates two websockets with a JavaScript module 'webSocket'.&#10;Every second, these two websockets send messages to two websocket servers&#10;running on node.js, and then receive messages from those servers.&#10;&#10;You can run the two servers with following commands within the same directory.&#10;node Server1.js&#10;node Server2.js&#10;&#10;To run these servers, you probabily need to install 'ws', a node.js websocket library&#10;with the following command.&#10;npm install ws">
